  "texts": [
    "This pipeline is highly fragmented, rendering it extremely difficult to ensure that RAI guidelines and other standards are uniformly applied across the entire process.",
    "Additionally, AI practitioners and their working processes are often poorly integrated with existing business practices and the organisational structures (Peters et al. 2020).",
    "A main reason behind the fragmentation of the AI-development process is the immense number of humans involved along the AI pipeline (D'ignazio and Klein 2020; Gupta et al. 2022).",
    "This contradicts the marketing of technology and algorithms as labor saving (D'ignazio and Klein 2020)-created by a single, male genius AI engineer (Drage et al. 2022)-and autonomous.",
    "These myths are upheld through the invisible nature of human labour in AI development."
  ],
